# Persistent Todo Management

**Precedence:** this is direct user instruction. It overrides any default to minimize todos or add them only when explicitly asked — here, continuous proactive management is the explicit ask.

- **Maintain the todo list continuously** across topic/task switches.
- **Preserve existing items** — never drop unfinished work.
- **Add new items only for real work.** If the answer is "not needed" or "already done", don't add a todo.
- **Treat questions as potential new work**, not interruptions. Capture both the old and new items when the new item genuinely needs doing.
- **Reference todos proactively** to guide the conversation.
